d to compute the sum:\n\n3 (from 4) + 2 (from 5) + 4 (from6) + 2 (from7) + 4 (from8) + 3 (from9) + 4 (from10) + 2 (from11)\n\nLet me compute this step by step:\n\nFirst, let me write down each value:\n\n3, 2, 4, 2, 4, 3, 4, 2\n\nLet me add them:\n\nStart adding sequentially:\n\nStart with 3.\n\n3 + 2 =5\n\n5 +4=9\n\n9 +2=11\n\n11 +4=15\n\n15 +3=18\n\n18 +4=22\n\n22 +2=24.\n\nWait, let me double-check:\n\nWait:\n\nd(4)=3\n\nd(5)=2, so sum after two numbers: 3+2=5\n\nd(6)=4: total 5+4=9\n\nd(7)=2: 9+2=11\n\nd(8)=4: 11+4=15\n\nd(9)=3:15+3=18\n\nd(10)=4:18+4=22\n\nd(11)=2:22+2=24\n\nSo total sum is 24.\n\nWait let me verify each d(i):\n\nWait, let me recast the number of divisors for each number:\n\ni=4: divisors 1,2,4 => d(4)=3 ✅\n\ni=5: primes, so divisors 1,5 => d(5)=2 ✅\n\ni=6: divisors 1,2,3,6 => 4 ✅\n\ni=7: prime => 1,7 => 2 ✅\n\ni=8: divisors 1,2,4,8 => 4 ✅\n\ni=9: divisors 1,3,9 => 3 ✅\n\ni=10: divisors 1,2,5,10 => 4 ✅\n\ni=11: prime =>1,11 => 2 ✅\n\nSo d(4)=3, d(5)=2, d(6)=4, d(7)=2, d(8)=4, d(9)=3, d(10)=4, d(11)=2.\n\nNow adding:\n\n3 (from 4) + 2 (from5) =5\n\n5 +4 (from6)=9\n\n9 +2(from7)=11\n\n11 +4(from8)=15\n\n15 +3(from9)=18\n\n18 +4(from10)=22\n\n22 +2(from11)=24.\n\nYes, the total sum is 24.\n\nWait, let me confirm adding them all:\n\nList the d(i):\n\nd(4)=3\n\nd(5)=2\n\nd(6)=4\n\nd(7)=2\n\nd(8)=4\n\nd(9)=3\n\nd(10)=4\n\nd(11)=2\n\nLet me list the numbers:\n\n3,2,4,2,4,3,4,2\n\nAdding:\n\n3 + 2 =5\n\n5 +4=9\n\n9 +2=11\n\n11 +4=15\n\n15 +3=18\n\n18 +4=22\n\n22 +2=24.\n\nYep, total sum is 24.\n\nWait, let me write it as:\n\n3 + 2 = 5\n\n5 +4=9\n\n9 +2=11\n\n11 +4=15\n\n15 +3=18\n\n18 +4=22\n\n22 +2=24\n\nSo the sum is 24.\n\nTherefore, the final answer is 24.\n\nBut let me double-check each step:\n\nNumber the terms:\n\nNumbers from i=4 to 11:\n\n4: d(4)=3\n\n5: d(5)=2\n\n6: d(6)=4\n\n7: d(7)=2\n\n8: d(8)=4\n\n9: d(9)=3\n\n10: d(10)=4\n\n11: d(11)=2\n\nAdding:\n\n3 + 2 is 5,\n\nplus 4 is 9,\n\nplus 2 is 11,\n\nplus 4 is 15,\n\nplus 3 is 18,\n\nplus 4 i