ultiply as such:\n\n2193 *3395.\n\nLet me write numbers:\n\n2193\ntimes 3395\n\nMaybe break down 3395 as 3000 + 300 + 90 +5.\n\nSo 2193*3000 =6,579,000\n\n2193*300 = 657,900\n\n2193*90 = 197, 4 something? Wait let me calculate 2193*90:\n\n2193*90=2193*9*10= 19737*10= 197,370\n\nThen 2193*5=10,965.\n\nThus sum all component products:\n\n6,579,000 (from 3000)\n\n+657,900(from 300)\n\n+197,370 (from90)\n\n+10,965 (from5)\n\nLet me add them step by step:\n\nFirst add 6,579"], label: None, reward: {'reward': -1.0, 'accuracy': 0, 'format_score': 0}
