 list in ascending order is 1, 4, 6, 14, 20.\n\nThe final answer is "1 4 6 14 20"\n\nSo I should write:\n\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nWait now wait let me confirm all the steps again. Let me write out all numbers and sort.\n\nOriginal numbers: 4, 6, 20, 14, 1.\n\nArrange ascending:\n\n1 is the smallest.\n\nNext, see the next numbers: 4,6, 14,20.\n\nOrder:1,4, remaining 6,14,20.\n\n6 is next, followed by 14, then 20.\n\nYes, the correct order is 1,4,6,14,20.\n\nTherefore the final boxed answer is "1 4 6 14 20".\n\n**Final Answer**\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nWait the instruction says to write the sorted numbers separated by spaces as one line, no more.\n\nSo just boxed the string like that without the quotes and treating it properly.\n\nI\'ll just state it concisely.\n\nThe final answer is:\n\n**The sorted list:** 1,4,6,14,20 → written within boxes as "1 4 6 14 20".\n\n**The single line is**\n\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nYes that should be it.\n\n**Final Answer**\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nWait no, wait the initial problem was given list is 4 6 20 14 1, or [4,6,20,14,1], and sorted ascending as 1,4,6,14,20.\n\nSo the exact final box will have "1 4 6 14 20".\n\nI think the final string needs to be \\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nYes, so final answer:\n\n**Final Answer**\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nThe thought process was pretty thorough; arranging numbers, double-checking, making sure order is correct before finalizing.\n**Final Answer**\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}\n\nWait double-checking calculated the initial problem again to ensure that I didn\'t misread.\n\nOriginal list: [4,6,20,14,1]. Let me recheck sorting:\n\nThe numbers to sort:\n\n1, 1 smallest.\n\nNext numbers:  next is 4, less than 6.\n\nThen 6, next:14 (because 14 compares next).\n\nThen 20 as last.\n\nSo sorted order is 1, 4, 6, 14,20. Yes correct.\n\nSo the list is correct.\n</think>\n\nThe sorted list in ascending order is 1, 4, 6, 14, 20. Thus, the final answer is represented as:\n\n\\boxed{1 4 6 14 20}<｜end▁of▁sentence｜>'], lab