e 280,500 +28,050 = 308,550\n\nThen + 1,683 = 308,550 +1,683 = 310,233. Same result.\n\nYes, 310,233 is accurate.\n\nThus product is 310,233. Therefore I can confirm that answer is 310,233.\n\n**Final Answer**\nThe product of 553 and 561 is \\boxed{310233}.\n</think>\n\nFirst, we use the distributive property by breaking down each number into parts and utilizing an alternative method to verify the accuracy of the multiplication. After multiple verification methods:\n\nWe know:\n- 553 × 561 can be computed efficiently using various multiplication strategies, leading to the result after careful calculation.\n\nThe result is obtained by breaking down the multiplication:\n- 553 × (500 + 60 + 1)  \n  computing 553×500=276500, 553×60=33180, 553×1=553, sum these to get the total product.\n\n276,500 + 33,180 = 309,680; then +553 gives 310,233.\n\nThus, verifying multiple times the product is indeed 310,233.\n\n\\[\n\\boxed{310233}\n\\]<｜end▁of▁sentence｜>"], label: None, reward: {'reward': 1.0, 'accuracy': 1, 'format_score': 1}
