t\'s count:\n\nWait they:\n\nOriginal given numbers are: 23, 8, 3, 24,19.\n\nLet me arrange them step by step.\n\nLet me list numerically:\n\nNumbers to sort:23, 8, 3,24,19.\n\nLet me arrange them step by step in increasing order.\n\nArrange the numbers:\n\nFirst arrange them:\n\n3, 8, 19, 23, 24. Because:\n\nThe smallest is 3, followed by 8. Then 19. Next 23, then 24.\n\nWait let me verify:\n\nComparing 3 vs 8: 3<8.\n\nNext numbers after 3: looking at the rest:\n\n19 is larger than, say,8 but smaller than 23,24 etc.\n\nWait let\'s list them step by step:\n\nOriginal list: 23, 8, 3, 24, 19.\n\nSort numerically:\n\n- Start by finding the minimum number.\n\nThe minimum number among these is 3, since it is the smallest.\n\nRemove 3 from the list and place it first.\n\nRemaining numbers:23,8,24,19.\n\nNext, find the smallest in remaining: 8, as it\'s the next smallest number.\n\nAdd 8 next.\n\nNow remaining numbers:23,24,19.\n\nNext smallest is 19.\n\nThen 23, then 24.\n\nSo sorted order is 3,8,19,23,24.\n\nWait let me check numbers all included:\n\nCheck each once:\n\nStarting the sorted list: 3 comes first, then 8, then smallest of remaining (19), next 23, 24.\n\nSo 3,8,19,23,24.\n\nYes that should be the ascending order.\n\nLet me confirm by checking each adjacent.\n\nCheck if 3 <8: yes. Next 8<19: yes. 19<23: yes, 23<24: yes.\n\nSo sorted list is 3, 8, 19, 23,24.\n\nTherefore arranging those five numbers in order:\nThe sorted sequence is 3, 8, 19, 23, 24.\n\nSo writing them separated by spaces: "3 8 19 23 24".\n\nTherefore the final answer should be "3 8 19 23 24".\n\nJust to double-check:\n\nLet me take the input list: 23,8,3,24,19\n\nSorting them:\n\nThe numbers are:23,8,3,24,19.\n\nLet me write them and sort:\n\nMove step by step sorting:\n\nLet me sort:\n\nSort the numbers using a method.\n\nWe can arrange numbers by their value.\n\nList the numbers: 23, 8, 3,24,19.\n\nConvert each:\n\n3, 8,23,19,24.\n\nWait Wait alternative approach: list all numbers.\n\nList the five numbers in the order given and sort them.\n\nOriginal numbers:\n\nNumber one:23,\nNumber two:8,\nNumber three:3,\nNumber four:24,\nNumber five:19.\n\nSort in ascending order:\n\nFirst numbers compare:\n\nThe smallest number is 3, then next smallest is 8, then 19, next 23, and the largest 24.\n\nSo sorted ascending order is:3, 8, 19,23,24.\n\nYes, so arranging the given list in order which matches our sorted numbers would be 3 8 19 23 24.\n\nSo I should write: "3 8 19 23 24".\n</think>\n\nThe sorted list in ascending order is:\n\n3 8 19 23 24\n\nSo, the output will be:\n\n3 8 19 23 24\n\nThe final answer is:\n\n\\boxed{3 8 19 23 24}\n\nWait, actually the initial list needs to be from the given numbers. Wait let me double-check my sorting.\n\nWait the original list is:23 8 3 2'], label: None, reward: {'reward': 1.0, 'accuracy': 1, 'format_score': 1}
